From c50c4fb0cb62cbacfe45694f99f2de09b86d62df Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cyrill Gorcunov <gorcunov@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 May 2019 17:15:40 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 016/119] kernel/sys.c: prctl: fix false positive in
 validate_prctl_map()

[ Upstream commit a9e73998f9d705c94a8dca9687633adc0f24a19a ]

While validating new map we require the @start_data to be strictly less
than @end_data, which is fine for regular applications (this is why this
nit didn't trigger for that long).  These members are set from executable
loaders such as elf handers, still it is pretty valid to have a loadable
data section with zero size in file, in such case the start_data is equal
to end_data once kernel loader finishes.

As a result when we're trying to restore such programs the procedure fails
and the kernel returns -EINVAL.  From the image dump of a program:

 | "mm_start_code": "0x400000",
 | "mm_end_code": "0x8f5fb4",
 | "mm_start_data": "0xf1bfb0",
 | "mm_end_data": "0xf1bfb0",

Thus we need to change validate_prctl_map from strictly less to less or
equal operator use.

